,"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Prior Provisions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A prior section 7608 was renumbered ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t26/s7613"},"text":"section 7613 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id47773a79-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2011—Subsec. (c)(1)(A)(i)(II). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/350/s5/f/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–350, § 5(f)(1)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “sections 6301(a) and (b)(1)–(3) and 6306” for “sections 11(a) and 22”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(1)(A)(i)(III). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/350/s5/f/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–350, § 5(f)(2)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “chapter 45” for “section 255”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(1)(A)(i)(V). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/350/s5/f/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–350, § 5(f)(3)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “section 3901” for “section 254(a) and (c)”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2008—Subsec. (c)(6). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/343"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–343","children":[],"tail":" struck out par. (6). Text read as follows: “The provisions of this subsection—"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(A) shall apply after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1988-11-17"},"text":"November 17, 1988","children":[],"tail":", and before "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-01-01"},"text":"January 1, 1990","children":[],"tail":", and"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(B) shall apply after the date of the enactment of this paragraph and before ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2008-01-01"},"text":"January 1, 2008","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"All amounts expended pursuant to this subsection during the period described in subparagraph (B) shall be recovered to the extent possible, and deposited in the Treasury of the United States as miscellaneous receipts, before ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2008-01-01"},"text":"January 1, 2008","children":[],"tail":".”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2006—Subsec. (c)(6). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/432"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–432","children":[],"tail":" substituted “2008” for “2007” in subpar. (B) and concluding provisions."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2005—Subsec. (c)(6). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/135"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–135","children":[],"tail":" substituted “"},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2007-01-01"},"text":"January 1, 2007","children":[],"tail":"” for “"},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2006-01-01"},"text":"January 1, 2006","children":[],"tail":"” in subpar. (B) and concluding provisions."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2003—Subsec. (c)(1)(A)(i)(IV). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/178"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–178","children":[],"tail":" substituted “title 40, United States Code” for “title 40”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2002—Subsec. (c)(1)(A)(i)(IV). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/217"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–217","children":[],"tail":" substituted “"},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t40/s8141"},"text":"section 8141 of title 40","children":[],"tail":"” for “"},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t40/s34"},"text":"section 34 of title 40","children":[],"tail":", United States Code”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2000—Subsec. (c)(6). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/554"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–554","children":[],"tail":" substituted “"},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2006-01-01"},"text":"January 1, 2006","children":[],"tail":"” for “"},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2001-01-01"},"text":"January 1, 2001","children":[],"tail":"” in subpar. (B) and concluding provisions."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1998—Subsec. (b)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/206"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–206","children":[],"tail":" struck out “or of the Internal Security Division” after “Intelligence Division”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1996—Subsec. (c)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/316"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–316","children":[],"tail":" struck out “and the Comptroller General of the United States” after “Secretary”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(4)(B)(ii). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/168/s1205/c/1/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–168, § 1205(c)(1)(A)","children":[],"tail":", (B), struck out “preceding the period” after “in the 1-year period” and “and” at end."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(4)(B)(iii), (iv). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/168/s1205/c/1/C"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–168, § 1205(c)(1)(C)","children":[],"tail":", added cls. (iii) and (iv) and struck out former cl. (iii) which read as follows: “the number, by programs, of undercover investigative operations closed in the 1-year period preceding the period for which such report is submitted and, with respect to each such closed undercover operation, the results obtained and any civil claims made with respect thereto.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(5)(C). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/168/s1205/c/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–168, § 1205(c)(2)","children":[],"tail":", reenacted heading without change and amended text generally. Prior to amendment, text read as follows: “The terms ‘undercover investigative operation’ and ‘undercover operation’ mean any undercover investigative operation of the Service—"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(i) in which—","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(I) the gross receipts (excluding interest earned) exceed $50,000; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(II) expenditures, both recoverable and nonrecoverable (other than expenditures for salaries of employees), exceed $150,000; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(ii) which is exempt from section 3302 or 9102 of title 31, United States Code.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Clauses (i) and (ii) shall not apply with respect to the report required under subparagraph (B) of paragraph (4).”","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(6). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/168/s1205/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–168, § 1205(b)","children":[],"tail":", added par. (6)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1990—Subsec. (c)(1)(B). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/508/s11704/a/32"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–508, § 11704(a)(32)","children":[],"tail":", struck out comma after “operations”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(5)(C). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/508/s11704/a/33"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–508, § 11704(a)(33)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “interest” for “interested” in cl. (i)(I) and “title 31” for “title 3” in cl. (ii)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1988—Subsec. (b)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/690/s7601/c/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–690, § 7601(c)(1)","children":[],"tail":", substituted comma for “or” before “any other” and inserted “, or any other law for which the Secretary has delegated investigatory authority to the Internal Revenue Service,” after “responsible”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/690/s7601/c/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–690, § 7601(c)(2)","children":[],"tail":", added subsec. (c)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1976—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/455"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–455","children":[],"tail":" struck out “or his delegate” after “Secretary” wherever appearing."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1962—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/863"},"text":"Pub. L. 87–863","children":[],"tail":" redesignated existing provisions as subsec. (a), added subsec. (a) heading, and added subsec. (b)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id47773a7a-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id47773a7b-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2008 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/343/dC/tIV/s401/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–343, div. C, title IV, § 401(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2008-10-03"},"text":"Oct. 3, 2008","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/122/3875"},"text":"122 Stat. 3875","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/110/343/dC/tIV/s401/b"},"text":"“The amendment made by this section [amending this section] shall apply to operations conducted after the date of the enactment of this Act [","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2008-10-03"},"text":"Oct. 3, 2008","children":[],"tail":"].”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":